<font color="#FF0000">THE POEMS DO YOU PROUD</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 21 22:17:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Thank You, Robert, for the collection of your poetry. It is nice to see it all together and feel the power of your writing. You say things, inbetween your words, that send shivers down my spine, and yet lift my hopes, that somewhere, mankind can be good.  <br><br>
Good poetry deserves to stand alone, like a good painting, seperate from the rest, lighted up by a spot, so that the others can enjoy it.  This thread is yours, and you have answered the call well.  I for one, wish to thank you for the gift of sharing. I will return here often.
